In large bowl, beat egg slightly. Stir in cereal, milk, onion, Worcestershire, salt, mustard and pepper. Let stand about 5 minutes, until cereal softens. Beat well. Add ground beef; mix well. Shape into loaf. Place in shallow foil-lined baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 180 degrees C (350 degrees F) about 45 minutes or until cooked in centre. Serve with Mushroom Sauce. Mushroom Sauce: In medium saucepan over low heat (or in microwave), heat mushroom soup and wine, stirring frequently, until mixture boils. Spoon sauce over sliced meatloaf.